article.headline: Georgia Southern 63, Elon University 45
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Georgia Southern tied a school record for fewest points allowed in a half, giving up just 12 in the second half to Elon in a 63-45 victory Monday night. Elton Nesbitt scored 15 points to lead the Eagles (14-7, 5-3 Southern Conference), who shot just 43.3 percent from the field but still far surpassed Elon's 28.8 percent, including just 13.8 percent in the second half. GSU held the Phoenix (10-11, 6-2 SoCon) scoreless for the first two and a half minutes of the game, forcing three quick turnovers. The game went back and forth over the next four minutes, but Elon pulled away for a 33-27 lead at the half. Georgia Southern outscored Elon 24-5 over the first 11 minutes of the second half, holding the Phoenix without a field goal for over four minutes. Colin Wyatt led Elon with 10 points and seven rebounds.
